Worst Prof I had so far. Here's Why: 1. She promised us that she will upload lecture slides, and she doesn't put them on blackboard. I had to ask her multiple times in email to upload the slides for exam prep. 2. ALOT OF READING; don't take this course for a bird. 3. If you're bad at essays, avoid it. She marks hard. Professor Ambros is extremely enthusiastic and energetic. She demands a lot of reading and involvement from the students and it is totally worth doing. The works she chooses to teach are captivating. All the readings were done online and she was always quick replying to my emails. I would recommend taking courses with her, especially the COL ones.
She tells you to email her with questions, yet she never replies to any of them. Not clear at all during lectures. She does not provide proper help to students.

She requires all papers to be submitted via email yet she doesn't know how to use a computer. She doesn't answer questions in a helpful manner. She is combative with students that have differing opinions. If she taught a course I required for my degree, I would seriously consider switching my major.

demanding, brilliant, and kind.  an amazing professor.  what you gain from the course depends on what you put into it, but her classes are always fascinating and she always makes time for her students. would highly recommend any of her courses.
